  transition: transform 1s, background-color 10s, color 10s;
}

.element:hover {
  transform: scale(1.5);
  background-color: #ff0000;
  color: #ffffff;
}
```

In this code, when you hover over the `.element` element, it will change its `background-color` and `color` properties from `#dddddd` and `#000000` to `#ff0000` and `#ffffff` respectively over a duration of 10 seconds due to the transition effect specified. Additionally, it will change its `transform` property from `scale(1)` to `scale(1.5)` over a duration of 1 second, creating a zoom effect. You can adjust the duration and values of the `transform`, `background-color`, and `color` properties to achieve your desired effect.

